Sentencas: Herein, praseodymium nitrate is infiltrated into Gd doped ceria (GDC) backbone and fired at 600 degrees C to form a composite oxygen electrode Pr6O11/GDC.
Titulo: An innovative efficient oxygen electrode for SOFC: Pr6O11 infiltrated into Gd-doped ceria backbone

Sentencas: Electrochemical measurements show very low polarization resistance, Rp = 0.028 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C. A single cell made of a commercial Ni-YSZ/YSZ half cell and of the infiltrated cathode is able to deliver a maximum power density of 825 rnW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C. Ageing of this cell for 840 h, at 600 degrees C and 0.5 A cm(-2), shows a degradation rate lower than 1%.
